long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1222163 Example of poedit window
Description of problem: After update of wxGTK3, the main window of poedit is unusable.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): wxGTK3-3.0.2-29.fc25.x86_64 poedit-1.8.11-1.fc25.x86_64 wxBase3-3.0.2-29.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Update wxGTK3 to wxGTK3-3.0.2-29 2. Launch poedit and open a PO file 3. Fields of PO file are covered by some strange gray widget.
Actual results: Screenshot is attached, main window of Poedit is unusable.
Expected results: Fields should be visible.
Additional info: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-b372d67ade
Yes, I can reproduce the problem. It looks like the problem does not exist with latest wx git, so there is probably another patch that I need to cherry-pick. Thanks for the report.
